Ernest Moniz has been confirmed as the next Secretary of Energy by the Senate. President Obama praises Moniz as a world-class scientist and leader with expertise in various energy sources. Moniz shares the President's belief that the US should lead in developing sustainable energy sources, creating new jobs and industries, and addressing climate change. The President looks forward to Moniz's counsel on energy security, nuclear security, clean energy technologies, and job competition in the 21st century.